<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-18T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-18T20:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">548.G1/30: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hamilton</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Beck</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton, Bermuda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-18T21:00:00-04:00">April 18,
                                1943—9 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received April 19—12:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>113. From Dodds for Long and Atherton.<note n="24" xml:id="d117fn24">Ray
                            Atherton, Acting Chief of the Division of European Affairs.</note>
                        Congressman Bloom believes that the question of Polish-Jewish refugees in
                        Russia should be brought up but not determined sometime before end of
                        Conference. He feels that delegation should be able to reply in the
                        affirmative if query made on this point by press or interested parties upon
                        conclusion of Conference. Please instruct. [Dodds.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beck</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>